The paper deals with the Metric Dimension problem, which is a graph theory problem and falls under the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The paper also discusses the parameterized complexity and approximation hardness of the problem, which are topics related to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The reduction used in the paper involves graphs with maximum degree three, which is a topic related to Computational Geometry (cs.CG) category. Finally, the paper discusses the inapproximability of the problem, which is a topic related to Graph Theory (cs.GT) category.
